{"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusProxyRef","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusProxyRef\/InitableProtocol-Implementations"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Initializes the object implementing the interface."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"init_"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV"},{"text":"? = nil) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This method is intended for language bindings. If writing in C,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_initable_new()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" should typically be used instead."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The object must be initialized before any real use after initial"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"construction, either with this function or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_async_initable_init_async()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Implementations may also support cancellation. If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" is not "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"then initialization can be cancelled by triggering the cancellable object","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from another thread. If the operation was cancelled, the error"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancelled"},{"type":"text","text":" will be returned. If "},{"code":"cancellable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is not "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the object doesn’t support cancellable initialization the error"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"notSupported"},{"text":" will be returned.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If the object is not initialized, or initialization returns with an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"error, then all operations on the object except "},{"code":"g_object_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_object_unref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" are considered to be invalid, and have undefined"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"behaviour. See the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"#iface@Gio.Initable#description","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for more details."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Callers should not assume that a class which implements "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable"},{"text":" can be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"initialized multiple times, unless the class explicitly documents itself as","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"supporting this. Generally, a class’ implementation of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"init()"},{"text":" can assume","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(and assert) that it will only be called once. Previously, this documentation","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"recommended all "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","type":"reference"},{"text":" implementations should be idempotent; that","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"recommendation was relaxed in GLib 2.54."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If a class explicitly supports being initialized multiple times, it is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"recommended that the method is idempotent: multiple calls with the same","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"arguments should return the same results. Only the first call initializes","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the object; further calls return the result of the first call."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"One reason why a class might need to support idempotent initialization is if","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"it is designed to be used via the singleton pattern, with a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObjectClass.constructor"},{"text":" that sometimes returns an existing instance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"In this pattern, a caller would expect to be able to call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_initable_init()"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on the result of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_new()"},{"text":", regardless of whether it is in fact a new","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/dbusproxyref\/init_(cancellable:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusProxyRef\/init_(cancellable:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Method","extendedModule":"GIO","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:3GIO16InitableProtocolPAAE5init_11cancellableSbAA14CancellableRefVSg_tKF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO12DBusProxyRefV","title":"init_(cancellable:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"init_"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV"},{"text":"?) ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"modules":[{"name":"GIO"}]},"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"#iface@Gio.Initable#description":{"type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"description"}],"url":"#iface@Gio.Initable#description","identifier":"#iface@Gio.Initable#description","title":"description"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/DBusProxyRef":{"role":"symbol","title":"DBusProxyRef","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusProxyRef","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDBusProxy"},{"type":"text","text":" is a base class used for proxies to access a D-Bus"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"interface on a remote object. A ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDBusProxy"},{"type":"text","text":" can be constructed for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"both well-known and unique names."}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DBusProxyRef"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"DBusProxyRef"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/dbusproxyref"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/AsyncInitable":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitable","title":"AsyncInitable","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/asyncinitable","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AsyncInitable","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AsyncInitable","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","abstract":[{"code":"GAsyncInitable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is an interface for asynchronously initializable objects."}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/DBusProxyRef/init_(cancellable:)":{"abstract":[{"text":"Initializes the object implementing the interface.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"init_"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef"},{"text":"?) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"}],"title":"init_(cancellable:)","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusProxyRef\/init_(cancellable:)","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/dbusproxyref\/init_(cancellable:)"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/CancellableRef":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/cancellableref","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GCancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" allows operations to be cancelled."}],"title":"CancellableRef"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/DBusProxyRef/InitableProtocol-Implementations":{"abstract":[],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/dbusproxyref\/initableprotocol-implementations","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusProxyRef\/InitableProtocol-Implementations","title":"InitableProtocol Implementations","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","kind":"article"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Initable":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/initable","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Initable","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"Initable","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GInitable"},{"type":"text","text":" is implemented by objects that can fail during"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"initialization. If an object implements this interface then","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"it must be initialized as the first thing after construction,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"either via [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Initable.init"},{"text":"] or [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.AsyncInitable.init_async"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(the latter is only available if it also implements [iface","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitable","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"])."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Initable"}]}}}